# Python Port Scanner

## Description
A beginner Python cybersecurity project that scans a target system to identify open TCP ports.

## Features
- Takes IP address or hostname as input
- Converts hostname to IP
- Scans ports 1â€“1024
- Displays open ports and services

## Technologies Used
- Python
- socket module

## How to Run
1. Run `python port_scanner.py`
2. Enter target IP or hostname
3. View open ports
